INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (647, 1, '2012-10-13 19:23:39', '2012-10-13 19:23:39', '<h1>Matt Tyas â€” Web/UX Designer and Front-end Developer</h1>\r\n\r\nI currently work for the web team at the <a href="http://www.leeds.ac.uk">University of Leeds</a>. I split my time between my day job, freelance work, running <a href="http://www.manchestersfinest.com">manchestersfinest.com</a> and <a href="http://soundcloud.com/matt_tyas">making music</a>. From time to time I also write my <a href="/out-of-my-head/">blog</a>.\r\n\r\n<h2>But it wasn\'t always soâ€¦</h2>\r\n\r\nBack in the eighties, my HTML was cardboard and my CSS, Sellotape. I just loved making things. Inventions and contraptions to solve my every problems. Problems such as:\r\n<blockquote>â€œHow do I get a Malteser in my mouth without having to get out of bed or move any of my limbs?â€</blockquote>\r\n\r\nThis was how the, \'Tonka Truck Malteser Race Track Delivery Device â„¢\', or, \'TTMRTDD\', was born. I am currently in a legal battle with Apple over this one.\r\n\r\n<h2>The world\'s worst website</h2>\r\n\r\nWhen I was 13 I built a website. We had dial up Compuserve internet. It was called, "Matthew Tyas\'s website" (because I couldn\'t change the page title) and it consisted of a home page, and a contact page with nothing but a clip art email link that didn\'t work. In fact, none of the links worked. I managed, however, to upload one MS Paint image. It was a scrawl that said,\r\n<blockquote>â€œWelcome to the world\'s worst websiteâ€</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do you want to employ me yet? Wait, I\'ve not finished!</h2>\r\n\r\nSince then I have continued to build websites and applications. At first badly (oh god, so badly) but I was lucky enough to meet some inspirational people who have helped me along the way and, I also put a lot of hours in to build up my skills.\r\n\r\n<h2>Full circle</h2>\r\n\r\nNowadays I plan projects with users and client requirements in mind. I wireframe through sketching, rubbing out, sketching, opening omnigraffle, drawing again, screwing up paper, asking for an opinion, wondering why I never thought of that, smiling, crying, smiling again, prototyping, testing, drawing some more and then, finally I\'m allowed to open Photoshop and apply some polish. Then it\'s client approval (yeah, I wish it was always that simple) build, test, build, device test, build, browser test, build, cry because of the errors and inconsistencies (feel like the king of the internet when you fix them), test, build and finally&hellip; launch. Always the best, and also the most anti-climactic feeling in the world, I\'m sure you\'ll agree.\r\n\r\n<h2>So that\'s me</h2>\r\n\r\nDownload my CV for the nitty gritty, check out my portfolio for the visual stuff and of course check out <a href="http://www.manchestersfinest.com" target="_blank">manchestersfinest.com</a> (another plug &#8212; sorry).\r\n\r\n<div class="cv">\r\n<a href="#" class="download-cv" aria-hidden="true" data-icon="&#x25bc;" ><span>Download CV</span></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<em>Updated CV coming soon</em>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '16-revision-48', '', '', '2012-10-13 19:23:39', '2012-10-13 19:23:39', '', 16, 'http://matthewtyas.com/16-revision-48/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
