then set as the homepage and uses a custom template that pulls in the newest four portfolio pieces, an area with information on Mcrfinest, an area that pulls in the newest two blog posts.</li>\n	<li>I only have one category for the blog, called, \'blog\', to categorise with in the blog I will either simply use tags or, sub-categories of, \'blog\'. I am yet to decide this.</li>\n	<li>For my portfolio I created a, \'Work\' category and subcategories to sit under it. The work category page is displayed using</li>\n</ul>', 'Almost a new home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '120-revision-5', '', '', '2011-12-16 09:33:45', '2011-12-16 09:33:45', '', 120, 'http://matthewtyas.com/lab/matthewtyas/?p=126', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
