INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (578, 1, '2012-08-22 14:16:56', '2012-08-22 14:16:56', '<h1>This is me right now</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>I am a Web Designer and Front-end Developer who currently works for the web team at the <a href="http://www.leeds.ac.uk">University of Leeds</a>. I split my time between my day job, freelance work, running <a href="http://www.manchestersfinest.com">manchestersfinest.com</a> and <a href="http://soundcloud.com/matt_tyas">making music</a>. From time to time I also write my <a href="/out-of-my-head/">blog</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>But it wasn\'t always so&hellip;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Back in the eighties, my HTML was cardboard and my CSS, Sellotape. I just loved making things. Inventions and contraptions to solve my every problems. Problems such as: <em>"How do I get a Malteser in my mouth without have to get out of bed or move any of my limbs?"</em>, and so the, \'Tonka Truck Malteser Race Track Delivery Device &#0153;\', was born.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Welcome to the world\'s worst website</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When I was 13 I built a website. We had dial up Compuserve internet. It was called, "Matthew Tyas\'s website" (because I couldn\'t change the page title) and it consisted of a home page, and a contact page (with nothing but a clip art email link that didn\'t work). In fact, none of the links worked. I managed, however, to upload one MS Paint image. It was a scrawl that said, <em>"Welcome to the world\'s worst website"</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I did Art and Graphics and school but never felt I connected properly with the fine art world, I wanted to make things that people used and got pleasure from, but I equally I didn\'t find I wanted to work in 3D as a crafts person either. I had forgotten all about websites.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '16-revision-14', '', '', '2012-08-22 14:16:56', '2012-08-22 14:16:56', '', 16, 'http://matthewtyas.com/16-revision-14/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
