blank">Design &amp; Art Direction</a> I started to notice interactions, and user experience on web sites. At this point I started to realise that designing for the web was a type of design in itself. Design that needed to flex, grow and accomodate multiple situations and multiple use cases.\r\n\r\nFrom then on it was a dash to learn everything I could about web design, coding and UX.\r\n<h2>Today, this type of design still excites me the most.</h2>\r\nEvery time I approach a new project there are new techniques to implement. New approaches to RWD...\r\n\r\nSorry, I am still writing this thrilling storyâ€¦', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '16-revision-28', '', '', '2012-08-28 20:36:38', '2012-08-28 20:36:38', '', 16, 'http://matthewtyas.com/16-revision-28/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
