INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (613, 1, '2012-09-20 14:54:22', '2012-09-20 14:54:22', 'It\'s great to have a well tested starting point for your web projects and this is mine. It is by no means original. I borrow from <a href="http://html5boilerplate.com/" target="_blank">HTML5 Boilerplate</a>, <a href="http://stuffandnonsense.co.uk/projects/320andup/" target="_blank">320 and Up</a> while also adding javascript libraries and scripts I tend to use / need. None of this stuff goes into every project, butI find it useful to have it there from the start as much to jog my memory and of course save me some time. I have also integrated SASS (SCSS files) <a href="http://compass-style.org/help/tutorials/best_practices/" target="_blank">based on best practices I have read about</a>.\n\nThis structure thus far:\n<ul>\n	<li>crossdomain.xml</li>\n	<li>css\n<ul>\n	<li>screen.css (outputted css file)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>fonts (empty folder)</li>\n	<li><a href="http://humanstxt.org/" target="_blank">humans.txt</a></li>\n	<li>images\n<ul>\n	<li>Icons\n<ul>\n	<li>apple-touch-icon-57x57-precomposed.png</li>\n	<li>apple-touch-icon-72x72-precomposed.png</li>\n	<li>apple-touch-icon-114x114-precomposed.png</li>\n	<li>apple-touch-icon-144x144-precomposed.png</li>\n	<li>apple-touch-icon-144x144-precomposed.png</li>\n	<li>apple-touch-icon.png</li>\n	<li>favicon.ico</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>spacer.gif (for use with the <a href="http://unstoppablerobotninja.com/entry/fluid-images" target="_blank">imgSizer.js plugin</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>index.html (references a lot of stuff I may or may not later strip out)</li>\n<li>js (if I use these scripts they are be minified by codekit before deployment)\n<ul>\n    <li>libs\n    <ul>\n        <li>helper.js</li>\n        <li>html5shiv.js</li>\n        <li>imgsizer.js</li>\n        <li>jquery-1.8.1.js (local copy used as fallback)</li>\n        <li>modernizr-2.6.1.js</li>\n        <li>respond.js</li>\n        <li>selectivizr.js</li>\n    </ul>\n</li>\n    <li>plugins.js (such as an <a href="http://mths.be/placeholder" target="_blank">input placeholder polyfill</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/scottjehl/iOS-Orientationchange-Fix" target="_blank">IOS orientation change bug fix</a>)</li>\n    <li>scripts.js</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Readme.md</li>\n<li>robots.txt</li>\n<li>sass\n<ul>\n<li>480.scss</li>\n<li>600.scss</li>\n<li>768.scss</li>\n<li>992.scss</li>\n<li>1382.scss</li>\n<li>base.scss</li>\n<li>buttons.scss</li>\n<li>colour.scss</li>\n<li>elements.scss</li>\n<li>forms.scss</li>\n<li>icon-fonts.scss</li>\n<li>ie.scss</li>\n<li>mixins.scss</li>\n<li>page.scss</li>\n<li>print.scss</li>\n<li>reset.scss</li>\n<li>screen.scss</li>\n<li>site.scss</li>\n<li>tables.scss</li>\n<li>texture.scss</li>\n<li>typography.scss</li>\n<li>variables.scss</li>\n<li>x2.scss</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n\nI use Codekit for the SASS compilation and minification) and Tower to connect to Github.\n\nIf you want to have a look or point out any glaring errors <a href="https://github.com/matt-tyas/Matt-Tyas-SASS-boilerplate" target="_blank">check it out on Github here</a>. This is a purely personal take on the boilerplate trend and by no means  is perfect. I am going to look at integrating this into a Wordpress theme such as <a href="http://viewportindustries.com/products/starkers/" target="_blank">Starkers</a> for my own use also.', 'My HTML5, JS & SASS Boilerplate', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'open', '', 'my-html5-js-sass-boilerplate', '', '', '2012-10-19 18:52:20', '2012-10-19 18:52:20', '', 0, 'http://matthewtyas.com/?p=613', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
